    "body": "Thanks - I can now do what I was trying to do. :) But (unless I still haven't got it) there seems to be an oddity related to label='right', closed='left' - last example below.\n\nIn [88]: ts8h\nOut[88]: \n2012-01-01 00:00:00    0.546799\n2012-01-01 08:00:00    0.272687\n2012-01-01 16:00:00   -0.730920\n2012-01-02 00:00:00   -0.121706\n2012-01-02 08:00:00   -1.670595\n2012-01-02 16:00:00    1.415328\n2012-01-03 00:00:00   -0.433233\n2012-01-03 08:00:00    0.340239\n2012-01-03 16:00:00   -0.186495\n2012-01-04 00:00:00    0.689044\nFreq: 8H\n\n# OK\n# \"take the _first_ value from the left-closed interval, and labeled with the date from the left end of the interval\"\nIn [89]: ts8h.resample('D', closed='left', label='left', how='first')\nOut[89]: \n2012-01-01    0.546799\n2012-01-02   -0.121706\n2012-01-03   -0.433233\n2012-01-04    0.689044\nFreq: D\n\n#OK\n# \"take the _last_ value from the left-closed interval, and labeled with the date from the left end of the interval\"\nts8h.resample('D', closed='left', label='left', how='last')\nOut[95]: \n2012-01-01   -0.730920\n2012-01-02    1.415328\n2012-01-03   -0.186495\n2012-01-04    0.689044\nFreq: D\n\n#ODD\n# if the interval is open on the right, \n# shouldn't the date come from 2012-01-01 16:00:00?\nts8h.resample('D', closed='left', label='right', how='first')\nOut[96]: \n2012-01-02    0.546799\n2012-01-03   -0.121706\n2012-01-04   -0.433233\n2012-01-05    0.689044\nFreq: D\n"
